# Kiali Backstage Dependency Validation

## When To Use This Rule

- Dependency update PRs for the Kiali Backstage workspace
- Backstage version upgrades
- Changes to `package.json`, `yarn.lock`, or Playwright E2E tests in that workspace
- Any request to validate the Kiali Backstage frontend after dependency changes

## Repository Context

- The commands below assume a checkout of [`backstage/community-plugins`](https://github.com/backstage/community-plugins/), where the Kiali workspace lives at `workspaces/kiali`.

## Validation Workflow

1. Verify Node.js 22 before running any other step:
   - `node --version`
   - If the version is not `v22.x.x`, switch first with `nvm use 22` or install it if needed.
   - Abort validation until the Node.js version is correct to avoid false failures.

2. Verify the Kiali environment:
   - Confirm the Kiali pod is running: `kubectl get pods -n istio-system | grep kiali`
   - Confirm port-forwarding on port 20001: `lsof -i :20001 || netstat -tuln | grep 20001`
   - Confirm `KIALI_ENDPOINT` is configured, typically `http://localhost:20001`
   - If port-forwarding is missing, start it with `kubectl port-forward -n istio-system svc/kiali 20001:20001 &`

3. Run validation from the Kiali Backstage workspace root:
   - `cd workspaces/kiali`
   - `yarn install`
   - `yarn tsc`
   - `yarn test:e2e`

4. For deeper validation when needed:
   - Run `yarn playwright test --ui` to inspect failures interactively
   - Run `yarn start` and manually verify the app at `http://localhost:3000/kiali`

## Manual Review Checklist

- Verify the main tabs still work: Overview, Traffic Graph, Workloads, Services, Applications, Istio Config
- Verify namespace selection flows still work
- Verify charts, sparklines, drawers, icons, and buttons render correctly
- Check for browser console errors during manual navigation
- Review dependency changes for breaking changes or unexpected lockfile churn
- Verify compatibility with the targeted Backstage version
- Check the RHDH compatibility matrix when Backstage is updated: `https://github.com/redhat-developer/rhdh-plugin-export-overlays?tab=readme-ov-file#backstage-compatibility`

## Common Failure Patterns

- Wrong Node.js version:
  - Typical symptoms include native module build failures, dependency resolution issues, or cryptic test failures.
  - Fix by switching to Node.js 22 before continuing.

- Missing or broken port-forward:
  - Verify Kiali responds with `curl http://localhost:20001/kiali/api/status`
  - If needed, restart port-forwarding after stopping the stale process.

- Dependency conflicts:
  - Run `yarn dedupe`
  - Re-run `yarn install`

- TypeScript failures after updates:
  - Check whether related `@types/*` packages also need updates.
  - Review breaking changes in the upgraded packages.

## Expected Report Format

Summarize validation results with:

- Environment check: Node.js version, Kiali pod, port-forward status, endpoint status
- Installation: success or failure, plus any vulnerability findings
- Compilation: TypeScript pass/fail status
- E2E tests: passed/failed counts, duration, and failed tests if any
- Remaining manual review items
